import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import cartopy.crs as ccrs
import os

#input file and select top 50 earthquakes
ds = pd.read_csv(r"E:\zwk\code\as4\usgs_earthquakes.csv")
new = ds.sort_values('mag', ascending = False)[:50]

#plot
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(12, 7))
ax = plt.axes(projection=ccrs.Robinson(central_longitude=180))
cp = ax.scatter(new.longitude, new.latitude , c = new['mag'],cmap='Reds',edgecolors = 'k', transform = ccrs.PlateCarree())
ax.set_global()
ax.stock_img()
ax.set_title('Top 50 Earthquakes of 2014')
fig.colorbar(cp,shrink = 0.4, ticks = np.linspace(6.6, 8.2,9,8.2) ,label = 'magnitude')
plt.show()

#define fuction

def add_right_cax(ax, pad, width):
    # '''
    # 在一个ax右边追加与之等高的cax.
    # pad是cax与ax的间距.
    # width是cax的宽度.
    # '''
    axpos = ax.get_position()
    caxpos = mpl.transforms.Bbox.from_extents(
        axpos.x1 + pad,
        axpos.y0,
        axpos.x1 + pad + width,
        axpos.y1
    )
    cax = ax.figure.add_axes(caxpos)

    return cax

#figure box 
fig1 = plt.figure(figsize=(18, 18), dpi = 120)

ax1 = fig1.add_axes([0,2/3,2/3,1/3])
ax6 = ax1.twinx()
ax2 = fig1.add_axes([0,1/3,2/3,1/3],projection = ccrs.PlateCarree(central_longitude=0))
ax3 = fig1.add_axes([0,0,  2/3,1/3],projection = ccrs.PlateCarree(central_longitude=0))
ax4 = add_right_cax(ax2, pad=0.2, width=0.02)
ax5 = add_right_cax(ax3, pad=0.2, width=0.02)
